//Ejercicios
//Lección 1

// 1a. Use alert(...) to display 'Good Morning!' in a pop-up.
alert('Good Morning!');

//1b. Display your name in a pop-up.
alert('Alejandro');

//1c. Using math, calculate 10 + 5 in the console.
10 + 5

//1d. Calculate 20 - 5 in the Console.
20 - 5

//1e. Calculate 2 + 2 - 5 in the Console.
2 + 2 - 5

//1f. Use document.body.innerHTML = ...; to display 'Good Morning!' on the web page.
document.body.innerHTML = 'Good Morning';

//1g. Display your name on the web page.
document.body.innerHTML = 'Alejandro';

//1h. You order a T-shirt for $10, socks for $8, and dinner plates for $20. Use JavaScript to calculate the total cost of your order.
10 + 8 + 20

//1i. Your bank account has $100, you spend $20 for lunch, $50 for dinner, and earn $200 from your job.
100 - 50 + 200

//1j. Use document.body.innerHTML = ...; to make the web page blank.
document.body.innerHTML = '';


//Lección 2

//2a. At a restaurant, you order 1 soup for $10, 3 burger each for $3, and 1 ice-cream for $5. Calculate the cost.
10 + 3 * 3 + 5

//2b. You're at a restaurant with 2 friends (3 people in total) and make the same order as 2a. Calculate how much each persona pays.
(10 + 3 * 3 + 5) / 3

//2c. Calculate the total cost of a toaster ($18.50) and 2 shirts ($7.50) each.
(1850 + 2 * 750) / 100

//2d. Calculate a 10% tax for the total in excercise 2c.
((18.50 + 2 * 7.50) * 0.1) / 100

//2e. Calculate a 20% tax for the total in 2c.
((1850 + 2 * 750) * 0.2) / 100

//2f. Calculate the costs of the products.
(1899 + 2095 + 799) / 100;

//2g. Calculate the Total before Tax.
(1899 + 2095 + 799 + 499) / 100

//2h. Calculate the 10% tax exactly.
Math.round((1899 + 2095 + 799 + 499) * 0.1) / 100;

//2i. Calculate order total.
(1899 + 2095 + 799 + 499) / 100 + Math.round((1899 + 2095 + 799 + 499) * 0.1) / 100

//2j. Round a number down.
Math.floor(2.8);

//2k. Round a number up.
Math.ceil(2.2);

//2l. The temperature is 25°C. Calculate the temperature in Fahrenheit.
25 * (9/5) + 32

//2m. The temperature is 86°F. Calculate the temperature in Celsius.
(86 - 32) * (5/9)

//2n. The temperature is -5°C. Calculate the temperature in Fahrenheit.
(-5) * (9/5) + 32


//Lección 3

//3a. Create the text 'My name is:' as a string.
'My name is:'

//3b. Create your name as a string.
'Alex'

//3c. Using concatenation, add 2 strings from 3a and 3b together.
'My name is: ' + 'Alex'

//3d. At a restaurant, you order 1 coffee ($5) and 1 bagel ($3). Using math, calculate
//the total cost, and using concatenation, create the text: 'Total cost:$_'
'Total cost: $' + (5+3)

//3e. Do the same thing as 3d, but use a template string and interpolation.
`Total cost: $${5+3}`

//3f. Display the text from 3e in a popup.
alert(`Total cost: $${5+3}`);

//3g. You order 1 coffee ($5.99) and 1 bagel ($2.95). Using math, calculate the total cost,
//and using concatenation, create the text: 'Total cost: $_'
'Total cost: $' + (599+295)/100

//3h. Do the same thing as 3g, but use a template string and interpolation.
`Total cost: $${(599+295)/100}`

//3i. Display the text from 3h in a popup.
alert(`Total cost: $${(599+295)/100}`)

//3j. Using a multiline string, create the text form 3h and add  aline of text underneath:
//'Thank you, come again!'. Display both lines in a popup.
alert(`Total cost: $${(599+295)/100}
Thank you, come again!`)

//3k.
`Items(${2+2}) $${(2*2095+2*799)/100}`

//3l.
`Shipping & handling: ${(499+499)/100}`

//3m. 
`Total before tax: ${((2*2095+2*799)+(499+499))/100}`

//3n. 
`Estimated tax (10%): ${Math.round(((2*2095+2*799)+(499+499))*0.1)/100`


